The weekly revenue is calculated as follows:

- Each class earns \(15 \text{ students} \times \$15 = \$225\).
- She teaches \(5 \text{ classes/day} \times 5 \text{ weekdays} = 25\) classes during the week.
- On Saturday she teaches \(8\) additional classes.
- Total classes in the week: \(25 + 8 = 33\).

Total weekly earnings:
\[
33 \text{ classes} \times \$225 \text{ per class} = \$7,\!425.
\]
